cu590_con | 1 | Two folios of fine, light-colored, lightweight, thin paper, highly glossed and sparsely mottled with small reddish-brown fibers.  The margins are unusually soiled, torn, and roughened, and parts have lost the original gloss of the paper.  Although the two sheets are still partially glued together, they are worm-eaten along the inner margin.  Some of the gold leaf has peeled off, as have some of the colors, the white having suffered the most in this respect.
